# Git & GitHub

Version control is GitHub. Keep history clean and reviewable.

## Branches

- `main` is always deployable. Never commit directly to `main` for feature work.
- Branch names use the format: `feature/<linear-code>-<shortened-branch-name>`.
- The prefix is **only ever `feature` or `hotfix`** — no other prefixes (regardless of the
  ticket's `Type` label; a chore/docs ticket still uses `feature/`). Use `hotfix/` only for
  urgent fixes to production.
- Always include the **Linear ticket code** (lowercase, e.g. `jus-51`) followed by a short,
  hyphenated description.
- Examples: `feature/jus-51-testing-tooling`, `feature/jus-24-homepage-hero`,
  `hotfix/jus-99-feed-parsing-crash`.

> Note: branch prefixes (`feature`/`hotfix`) are separate from commit types. Commits still
> follow Conventional Commits (see below), so a `feature/` branch can contain `chore:` or
> `docs:` commits.

## Commits

**All commits — including every commit made by an AI agent — MUST follow the
[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org) format. No exceptions.**

Format:

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <description>

<optional body explaining the why>

<optional footer, e.g. BREAKING CHANGE: ... or Refs: JUS-123>
```

- **type** — one of: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `ci`, `perf`,
  `build`, `style`, `revert`.
- **scope** (optional) — the affected area/package, e.g. `feat(ui):`, `fix(tradetracker):`,
  `docs(design-system):`.
- **description** — imperative mood, lowercase, no trailing period (e.g. "add hero section").
- **breaking changes** — append `!` after the type/scope (`feat(ui)!:`) and/or add a
  `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.
- Keep commits **small and focused**; the body explains the **why**, not the what.
- Reference the related Linear ticket in the footer where relevant (e.g. `Refs: JUS-42`).
- Only commit when explicitly asked. Never commit secrets or `.env*` files.

A **commit-msg hook (commitlint)** enforces this format on every commit, and a **pre-commit
hook** (husky + lint-staged) formats staged files and runs `lint`, `type-check` and `test`
before a commit is accepted. Hooks install automatically via the `prepare` script on
`pnpm install`. Never bypass them with `--no-verify`.

## Pull requests

- Open PRs into `main`; keep them scoped and small where possible.
- Reference the related Linear ticket in the PR description.
- CI (lint + type-check + build) must pass before merge.
